Now let&#39;s suppose you change these values:

    boxes.length = 1;
    boxes.height = 1;
    boxes.width = 1;
This action doesn&#39;t change `boxes.fmax`, because it was initializaed with 0 and it doesn&#39;t call `getVol` again. If you want to change it, you can use a function `getFmax()` instead.

    float getFmax() {
        return this.getVol() / 40000;
    }
this function will return a different value calling `getVol()` every time.

When a variable is assigned to a math operation, it will be only calculated once. If you want it to change when you change one of the numbers in the math operation, you will need to re-assign it. Instead of using a variable, try using this function which will re-calculate the fmax value every time you want it.

```java
public float getFmax() {
    return this.getVol() / 40000;
}
```

